TITLE: Biden says his budget plan would extend Medicare to 2050 without adding to the deficit
SUMMARY: President Biden is proposing to raise taxes on people who make more than $400,000 per year to make sure there's enough money for Medicare.

TITLE: China accuses U.S. of containment and warns of potential conflict
SUMMARY: Chinese leader Xi Jinping's rare explicit criticism of the U.S. was followed on Tuesday by a barrage of scorn and criticism aimed squarely at Washington from China's new foreign minister.

TITLE: What to know about the new U.N. high seas treaty — and the next steps for the accord
SUMMARY: Right now, two-thirds of the ocean are regulated by a fragmented patchwork of agreements and organizations. This treaty plans to unite countries to improve the health of the ocean.

TITLE: What SNAP recipients can expect as benefits shrink in March
SUMMARY: Participants in the federal food program might want to reevaluate their eligibility level for SNAP — and consider other assistance programs — as a pandemic-era supplement ends this month.

TITLE: 'Dr. No' is a delightfully escapist romp and an incisive sendup of espionage fiction
SUMMARY: Pulitzer and Booker Prize finalist Percival Everett just won another prestigious award, the PEN/Jean Stein Award, for his newest book<em>

TITLE: A rundown of what's led to Atlanta's 'Cop City' protests
SUMMARY: Police arrested at least 35 people after activists set heavy equipment on fire. Tensions have been building for years over the plan to build a large police training facility.

TITLE: How (and why) this man plans to live underwater for 100 days
SUMMARY: Retired Navy officer Joseph Dituri is attempting to break the world record for living underwater, all in the name of science.

TITLE: Q: Who's unsurprised by shocking Fox News revelations? A: Ex-Fox journalists
SUMMARY: Evidence in Dominion Voting System's $1.6 billion defamation suit against Fox News has cast the network, its stars and its executives in a harsh light. Ex-Fox journalists say they're not surprised.

TITLE: Medical debt affects millions, and advocates push IRS, consumer agency for relief
SUMMARY: More than 50 consumer and patient groups want the Biden Administration to aggressively protect Americans from medical bills and debt collectors. The effort follows a KHN/NPR investigation.

TITLE: How Barnes & Noble turned a page, expanding for the first time in years
SUMMARY: After years on the brink, the bookseller is going for a plot twist: Sales are growing and the chain plans to open some 30 new stores. Here's what's changed.

TITLE: Tribes bury P-22, Southern California's famed mountain lion
SUMMARY: The cougar's death set off a debate between tribes in the Los Angeles area and wildlife officials over whether scientists could keep samples of the animal's remains for future testing and research.

TITLE: Canada announces a probe to examine possible Chinese election interference
SUMMARY: The announcement of a probe of possible Chinese influence in Canadian elections follows a newspaper report stating that China preferred to see Trudeau's Liberals re-elected in the 2021 election.

TITLE: A man allegedly tried to tamper with a plane to Boston and stab a flight attendant
SUMMARY: The suspect was arrested at the Boston Logan International Airport after allegedly tampering with a side door and the emergency slide, and later allegedly lunged at a flight attendant.

TITLE: The U.S. and Mexico are working together to find 4 Americans who were kidnapped
SUMMARY: The abduction took place on the streets of Matamoros, Mexico. The FBI is offering a $50,000 reward for the return of the Americans and the arrests of those involved.

TITLE: 5 DeSantis allies now control Disney World's special district. Here's what's next
SUMMARY: A parents' rights activist, a Christian nationalist and three lawyer donors now have control over Walt Disney World's development capabilities, thanks to a bill signed by Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis.
